name: Suneido
description: Suneido is an interpreted, interactive programming language for Microsoft Windows first released in 2000. It is fully dynamically typed and uses automatic memory management; it is thus similar to Python, Tcl, Perl, Scheme, and Ruby. Suneido is developed as an open source project. The Suneido system includes the language, an integrated client–server relational database, and an integrated development environment. The latest release was made on April 9, 2011.
